\section{Final Project}

The final project is the centerpiece of this course. Students work in teams
of 2--3 to reproduce a recent ML paper and extend it with a novel experiment.

@Project milestones:
\begin{enumerate}
\item Week 4: Team formation and paper selection (1-page proposal).
\item Week 8: Progress report with initial reproduction results.
\item Week 13--14: Final presentation (15 min + 5 min Q\&A).
\item Week 15: Final report (8 pages, NeurIPS format).
\end{enumerate}@<param context:learning_goals><plan Evaluate whether these milestones give students enough structured checkpoints. Suggest additional milestones or peer-review stages that would improve project quality and catch issues early.><output REVISION PLAN: PROJECT MILESTONES

ANALYSIS: Current milestones provide only 4 checkpoints across 15 weeks, with a significant gap between Week 4 (proposal) and Week 8 (progress report). No peer-review component exists, which is essential for Goals 2 and 3.

RECOMMENDED ADDITIONS:

1. ADD Paper Comprehension Checkpoint (Week 6): 2-page technical summary of selected paper covering key claims, methodology, and reproduction strategy. Catches comprehension issues before implementation effort is wasted.

2. ADD Peer-Review of Progress Reports (Week 9): Each team reviews another team's progress report using a rubric covering experimental design, baseline selection, and statistical methodology. Builds critical evaluation skills (Goal 2) and gives teams time to course-correct.

3. ADD Ethics and Data Audit (Week 10): 1-page document covering dataset provenance, potential biases, and ethical considerations. Addresses Goal 4, which currently has no dedicated milestone.

4. ADD Draft Report with Peer Feedback (Week 12): Minimum 5-page draft followed by peer review focused on clarity, ablation completeness, and statistical validity. Prevents last-minute writing and reinforces Goal 3.

5. STRENGTHEN Week 8 Progress Report: Change to require at least one baseline comparison and a description of planned ablation experiments. Current wording is too vague.

REVISED MILESTONE SEQUENCE:
Week 4 -- Team formation and paper selection (1-page proposal)
Week 6 -- Paper comprehension summary (2 pages)
Week 8 -- Progress report with reproduction results, baseline comparison, and ablation plan
Week 9 -- Peer review of progress reports
Week 10 -- Ethics and data audit (1 page)
Week 12 -- Draft final report (min 5 pages) with peer feedback
Week 13-14 -- Final presentation (15 min + 5 min Q and A)
Week 15 -- Final report (8 pages, NeurIPS format)><hash 7626bad06992d0f5>

